DAY-18(FRIDAY)
Topics:
1)What is Delete Statement 
2) Difference between Delete,Drop,Truncate 
3)Delete statement with WHERE clause
4)Delete Duplicate Rows 

syntex:
DELETE FROM table_name
[where condition];

delete:used to clear the unwanted or absolute data from database and can be used to delete single row
drop: used to remove entire structure of the database 
truncate:used to remove all data from table but preserve the table structure 

DELETE multiple records using where clause as
DELETE FROM employee 
WHERE employeeID>2;

Delete Duplicate rows 
SELECT*FROM employee
GROUP BY employeeID HAVING COUNT(employeeName)>1; 

How to delete the record
1)Using distinct keyword
2)Using Group by and Having clause
3)Using Inner Join statement 
